text: Cora Sue Collins (April 19, 1927 - April 27, 2025) was an American child actress. She was known for her roles in Queen Christina, Anna Karenina, and All This, and Heaven Too. She retired from acting in 1945 at the age of 18. Collins died on April 27, 2025 at her home in Beverly Hills, California from problems caused by a stroke at the age of 98. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1927 births Category:2025 deaths Category:American child actors Category:American movie actors Category:Actors from West Virginia Category:Deaths from stroke
